Dialogue: 0,0:29:13.16,0:29:16.75,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,在二叠纪到三叠纪的地球上大量繁衍\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}prospered on Earth during the Permian-Triassic period.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:16.79,0:29:21.84,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,然后某些神秘事件几乎抹掉了当时所有的生命\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Then some mysterious event wiped out almost all life at that time.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:24.38,0:29:27.55,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,事实上那是最严重的灭绝事件\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}ln fact, it's the most severe extinction with respect...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:27.59,0:29:30.93,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,涉及了多少动植物的消亡\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to how many different animals and plants perished.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:30.97,0:29:35.81,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,那是我们地球生命史上最大的灭绝事件\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}lt's the biggest extinction event in the history of life on our planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:37.02,0:29:41.11,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,贝克正着手侦破这个史前命案\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Becker is on a mission to solve this prehistoric crime.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:41.15,0:29:44.69,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,类似于涉嫌杀死恐龙的K-T 撞击\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Like the K-T impact that probably killed the dinosaurs...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:44.74,0:29:46.61,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,她声称已发现证据表明\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}she claims to have uncovered evidence...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:46.65,0:29:51.45,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,有一颗巨大的小行星同样造成了二叠纪 - 三叠纪灭绝事件\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that a giant asteroid also caused the Permian-Triassic extinction...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:51.49,0:29:55.20,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,发生在1.85亿年前\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}which occurred about 185 million years earlier.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:59.33,0:30:01.38,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,在二叠纪至三叠纪期间\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}During the Permian-Triassic period...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:01.42,0:30:06.26,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我们的世界由一块超级大陆 即所谓的盘古大陆\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}ourworld was comprised of one supercontinent called Pangaea...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:06.30,0:30:09.18,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,以及一个超级大洋 即所谓的原始大洋构成\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and a super ocean called Panthalassa.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:11.30,0:30:12.64,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,按贝克的说法\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}According to Becker...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:12.68,0:30:15.68,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,一个7英里宽的物体撞进大洋\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}a seven-mile-wide object slammed into the ocean...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:15.73,0:30:17.98,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,靠近超级大陆的南端\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}near the southern tip of the supercontinent...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:18.02,0:30:20.27,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,就是现在的澳大利亚的西北角外\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}which is now off northwestAustralia.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:22.07,0:30:25.53,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,如果你站在2.5亿年前的海滩上\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}lfyou were standing on the beach 250 millions years ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:25.57,0:30:28.32,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,就有可能目睹这个与众不同的事件了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}you'd probably have a pretty good view of this particular event.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:28.36,0:30:32.49,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,你会看到一个巨大的物体 珠峰一般大小\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}You have a large body, the size of, say, Mount Everest...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:32.53,0:30:36.58,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,结实的身躯撞入大陆边缘\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}rigid body slamming into the continental margin...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:36.62,0:30:38.00,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,就在海岸边\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}along the actual beach...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:39.37,0:30:43.34,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,引发了大地震和大海啸\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}creating a huge earthquake, mega tsunamis...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:43.38,0:30:48.34,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,掀起数英里尘埃直达大气层\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}injecting miles and miles of dust debris up into the atmosphere...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:48.38,0:30:53.80,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,蔓延全球 遮天蔽日\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}distributing itself globally...in such a manner that it blocks sunlight out.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:53.85,0:30:56.52,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,你可以看到当时有几个月暗无天日\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}You could have had darkness for months at a time.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:56.56,0:30:58.98,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,这足以终止光合作用\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This is enough to shut down photosynthesis.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:59.02,0:31:01.02,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,那是食物链的顶端\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That's the top of the food chain...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:01.06,0:31:03.02,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,那就是涓滴效应\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and that just has a trickle-down effect.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:04.40,0:31:06.19,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,如果贝克的理论是正确的话\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}lf Becker's theory is correct...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:06.23,0:31:09.44,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,那么这个撞击将抹去地球自结合成\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}this impact could have wiped out most life on Earth...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:11.78,0:31:15.87,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,一个大陆及一个大洋以来的大部分生命\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}since it was concentrated on one continent and one ocean.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:18.25,0:31:21.00,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,这种等级的灭绝事件\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}An extinction event of this magnitude...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:21.04,0:31:24.00,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,将会导致完全的进化\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}would have allowed for complete evolutionary change...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:25.63,0:31:29.26,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,从而为恐龙的进化扫清障碍\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}thus paving the way for the dinosaurs to evolve.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:31.22,0:31:32.47,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,这只是因为\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}lt was only because...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:32.51,0:31:34.89,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,二叠纪 - 三叠纪灭绝事件的发生\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the Permian-Triassic extinction event occurred...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:34.93,0:31:37.93,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我认为恐龙得以进化某种程度上\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and what l consider to be somewhat attributed...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:37.97,0:31:42.23,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,应归因于这个撞击事件\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to this impact event...that the dinosaurs were able to evolve.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:44.27,0:31:48.40,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,二叠纪 - 三叠纪灭绝事件只留下很少的地质证据\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Little geological evidence remains of the Permian-Triassic extinction.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:48.44,0:31:52.03,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,只有极少量的2.5亿年前的岩石\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}There are very few 250-million-year-old rocks...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:52.07,0:31:53.24,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,留在地球上\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}left on Earth...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:53.28,0:31:56.12,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,那是因为它们随着板块构造被回收利用了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}because they've been recycled by plate tectonics.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:59.50,0:32:01.58,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,然而贝克说她在澳大利亚西北部的撞击坑\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But Becker says she's found traces...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:01.62,0:32:06.13,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,发现了踪迹\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}of the actual impact crater in northwestern Australia.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:13.80,0:32:19.51,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,被称为大灭绝的二叠纪 - 三叠纪灭绝\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The Permian-Triassic extinction...known as the Great Dying...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:19.56,0:32:23.44,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,是地球史上最大的灭绝事件\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}was the biggest extinction event in the history of planet Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:23.48,0:32:28.23,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,2.5亿年前九成的生命消失了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Ninety percent of all life perished 250 million years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:28.27,0:32:31.03,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,期间灭绝的生命远多于\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}More more creatures expired during this period...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:31.07,0:32:37.66,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,1.85亿年后灭绝恐龙的K-T 灭绝事件\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}than the K-T extinction that killed the dinosaurs...over185 million years later.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:37.70,0:32:42.20,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,二叠纪 - 三叠纪灭绝的原因尚无定论\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The cause of the Permian-Triassic extinction has gone unsolved.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:45.00,0:32:48.46,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,然而现在科学家路安·贝克及其他人\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But now, research scientist Luann Becker and others...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:48.50,0:32:50.50,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,认为是小行星导致了这个事件\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}think an asteroid caused the event...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:53.42,0:32:56.13,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,他们已经发现了一个潜在的撞击坑\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and they've uncovered a possible impact crater...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:56.18,0:32:59.85,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,就沉睡于澳大利亚西北部的近海里\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}buried under sediments offshore of northwestern Australia.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:01.39,0:33:03.81,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我们相信我们已经发现了那次撞击事件\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We believe we found a very good candidate...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:03.85,0:33:06.65,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,很好的候选者\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}forwhat is the impact event itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:06.69,0:33:09.48,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,它越古老 其结构就越复杂得多\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}lt's much older, it's a lot more complicated...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:09.52,0:33:12.32,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,地质过程就越漫长\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and a lot more geologically processed.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:12.36,0:33:14.70,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,它不再是完美的循环\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}lt's not a perfect circle anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:14.74,0:33:16.82,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,它看上去不像是靶心\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}lt doesn't look like a bull's-eye.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:16.86,0:33:19.16,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,大部分二叠纪岩石已经消失了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Most of the Permian rocks have been subducted...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:19.20,0:33:22.12,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,早就灭失 风化掉了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and they're long gone or eroded away.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:25.42,0:33:27.00,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,那里作为撞击的证据\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The evidence for an impact there...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:27.04,0:33:28.92,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,很边缘且极具争议\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is marginal and highly controversial.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:30.13,0:33:32.00,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,有些科学家质疑\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Some scientists are skeptical...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:32.05,0:33:35.80,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,贝克发现了二叠纪 - 三叠纪年代的撞击坑\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that Becker has found an impact crater...from the Permian-Triassic period.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:37.64,0:33:41.93,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,尚未发现有合适的撞击坑能匹配二叠纪 - 三叠纪年代\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}No good crater has been found to match the Permian-Triassic age.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:41.97,0:33:46.85,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,有一个主张认为澳大利亚西海岸存在一种构造\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}There was a claim of a structure off of the west coast ofAustralia...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:46.89,0:33:52.90,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,但是并不明显 并不像K-T撞击那样清晰\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but it's not as clean and as clear as the K-T crater.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:52.94,0:33:54.44,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我们没有看到确凿的证据\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We don't have a smoking gun.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:56.74,0:33:59.87,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,但是路安·贝克声称自己已经找到了确凿的证据\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But Becker claims she has found the smoking gun.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:59.91,0:34:03.16,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,此外 她和她的团队前往南极\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}What's more, she and her team have traveled to Antarctica...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:03.20,0:34:09.50,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,澳大利亚 非洲 日本等地球上现存最古老岩石的地方\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Australia, Africa, and Japan, where the oldest rocks on Earth exist.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:09.54,0:34:13.05,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,他们声称已经发现了四十个撞击坑\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They claim to have found forty impact tracers.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:13.09,0:34:15.88,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,这些是地球外的矿物碎片\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}These are extraterrestrial mineral fragments...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:15.92,0:34:20.05,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,发现于二叠纪 - 三叠纪年代的岩层中\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}recovered from rock layers...dating to the Permian-Triassic period.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:22.93,0:34:28.56,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我们发现了我们认为是零星的撞击碎片\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We have found what we consider to be...little bits and pieces of impact debris...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:28.60,0:34:33.11,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,这确实看上去就像是陨石那样的东西\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}which literally looks like what we'd find...if we were looking at a meteorite.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:33.15,0:34:36.57,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,这有可能是一些撞击陨石碎片\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}lt's possible for some of the impact meteoritic debris...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:36.61,0:34:39.36,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,落下并保存在岩层里的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to fall back down and get preserved in the rock layer.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:40.78,0:34:45.74,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,尚未在二叠纪 - 三叠纪的岩层中发现铱\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}What hasn't been recovered...from the Permian-Triassic rock layer is iridium.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:45.79,0:34:49.83,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,这种陨石物质已经帮助让许多科学家相信了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}lt's the meteoritic substance...that helped to convince many scientists...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:49.87,0:34:55.67,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,是小行星撞击造成了6500万年前的恐龙灭绝\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that an asteroid impact caused the extinction of the dinosaurs...sixty-five million years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:58.42,0:35:01.93,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,同僚们试着吹毛求疵\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Colleagues want to try to get real nitpicky about...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:01.97,0:35:03.68,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,"啊 你也应该找到铱呀"\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}"Well, you should have found iridium, too."
Dialogue: 0,0:35:03.72,0:35:08.35,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我们并未在预料会发现的地方找到铱\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Well, we're not finding iridium...in some of the places we would expect to find it...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:08.39,0:35:11.02,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,比如 我们所带回的一些彗星物质中\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}like in some of the cometary material that we brought back.
